******
[2]
Date: Mon 7 Oct 2013
Source: Bernama [edited]
http://www.mysinchew.com/node/92362?tid=4


The Agriculture and Agro-based Industry Ministry will investigate the claim that chicken imported from Thailand was the cause of foodborne illness that killed 4 people in Kedah recently. Its minister, Datuk Seri Ismail Sabri Yaakob, said that, so far, the ministry had not received any report on this claim, but that it will be investigated to determine whether the imported chicken contained life-threatening bacteria.

"We will inform and seek the cooperation of the Health Ministry to further investigate the matter."

Four people died after consuming a chicken dish, "ayam masak merah," said to be contaminated with salmonella bacteria, served at a wedding feast in Kampung Huma, Tanjung Dawai in Merbok, Kedah on 28 Sep 2013.

